/-!
# SL-2: a genuine `Œ¶ ‚âÝ id` on the concrete ENTANGLED (singlet) sector

**Category:** 3-Local (a genuine `Œ¶ ‚âÝ id` on the concrete ENTANGLED (singlet) sector).

D1c-1 (`LF4/KahlerFlow.lean`) discharged the "`Œ¶ = id` in the concrete K√§hler
instance" debt for the GENERIC sector: `kSectorDataFlow` carries the non-identity
measure-preserving flow `Œ¶ = kFlow sh` (a free `T¬≤`-fibre translation), and
`kFlow_frequency_convergence` makes its Liouville-preservation *load-bearing* (it
pins the law of the evolved trials `kFlow sh ‚àò sample`).

This module does the same for the **entangled** sector ‚Äî the two-qubit singlet on
`Œ£ = ‚ÑÇ‚Ñô¬≥ √ó T¬≤` (`LF4/SingletKahler.lean`), SL-2. The singlet preparation
`ofK√§hlerPreparation` was built over `kSectorData` (`Œ¶ = id`); here it is rebuilt
over `kSectorDataFlow p‚ÇÄ sh` (`Œ¶ = kFlow sh ‚âÝ id`), and the per-sector frequency
capstone fires with the trials genuinely **evolved by the sector's own flow**.

The mechanism is exact and requires no new engine. An LF1 `OutcomeRegion`'s scored
event is `preEvent = Œ¶ ‚Åª¬π' Œ©` (`LF1/Outcomes.lean`), so with `Œ¶ = kFlow sh` the
capstone scores `X ‚Åª¬π' preEvent = (kFlow sh ‚àò X) ‚Åª¬π' kRegion` ‚Äî each sampled
microstate is pushed one flow-step before its outcome block is read. Liouville
preservation is load-bearing through `bridge_op_p`: the carving identity now reads
`kMuPsi (kFlow sh ‚Åª¬π' kRegion) = kMuPsi (kRegion) = P_st`, the first equality being
`kFlow_measurePreserving_muPsi` (the singlet analogue of `kFlow_measurePreserving`).
So the empirical frequency of the flow-evolved singlet trials still converges a.s.
to the Born weight `P_st`.

## Deliverables

* `kFlow_measurePreserving_muPsi` ‚Äî `kFlow sh` preserves the singlet fibre law
  `Œºœà = Œ¥_{[singlet]} ‚äó vol_{T¬≤}` (fixes the base ray, translates the fibre);
* `ofK√§hlerPreparationFlow` ‚Äî the singlet `PureSingletPreparation` over the
  `Œ¶ ‚âÝ id` sector `kSectorDataFlow p‚ÇÄ sh`;
* `ofK√§hlerPreparationFlow_phi_ne_id` ‚Äî its sector genuinely carries `Œ¶ ‚âÝ id`;
* `ofK√§hlerPreparationFlow_flow_frequency_convergence` ‚Äî the per-sector empirical
  frequencies of the trials **evolved by `kFlow sh`** converge a.s. to `P_st`.

## Honest scope (unchanged from D1c-1)

`kFlow` is a *free* fibre translation: a genuine measure-preserving `Œ¶ ‚âÝ id`, but
dynamically trivial (it is not a de-isolation / measurement flow, nor a
Hamiltonian flow generated by the K√§hler form; it moves only within the fibre over
a fixed ray). So this is the **structural** discharge of "`Œ¶ = id` in the concrete
*entangled* instance", making Liouville-preservation load-bearing on the singlet ‚Äî
NOT a derivation of the sector. **A5 is untouched** (the entangled sector /
Fubini‚ÄìStudy typicality is still posited; that is SL-1). Foundational-triple-only
/ Gleason-free, inherited from `ofK√§hlerPreparation` and the LF3 chain.
-/

@[expose] public section

open MeasureTheory Matrix Matrix.UnitaryGroup
open scoped LinearAlgebra.Projectivization
